Europe
----
[1] Ireland
Date: Thu 3 Nov 2011
Source: Irish Examiner [edited]
http://www.examiner.ie/breakingnews/ireland/139-cases-of-measles-recorded-in-two-months-526871.html


Almost one in 10 children who contracted measles over the summer
[2011] had to be hospitalised according to reports.

Some 139 cases of measles were recorded in August and September 2011
alone, with 11 of these admitted to hospital. Seven of these -- aged
between 5 and 9 -- were either not vaccinated against the disease or
were under-vaccinated.

According to the Health Protection Surveillance Centres, 265 cases
have been reported in 2011 with 90 percent of those in Dublin.

