[Auckland, Otago and Southland can be located in the
HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of New Zealand at:
http://healthmap.org/r/1hiF.

The authorities in New Zealand have been concerned about the risk of
spread of measles virus infection by airline passengers. While
examples of this have occurred, the short duration of internal flights
probably diminishes this hazard.

The transmission of measles within the United States has been
contained. In Europe, outbreaks continue, with France remaining the
centre of the epidemic. - Mod.CP]
